12:Tef7,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Blog","name":"Ember Sterling — Blog","description":"Field notes on UK SEO, web development, paid acquisition, and conversion for ambitious British brands.","url":"https://sterlingember.com/blog","inLanguage":"en-GB","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Ember Sterling","url":"https://sterlingember.com"},"blogPost":[{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"The 2026 UK Local SEO Playbook for Multi-Location Businesses","description":"A field-tested playbook for ranking across UK cities — Google Business Profile, location pages, schema, and citation strategy that actually moves rank in 2026.","url":"https://sterlingember.com/blog/uk-local-seo-playbook-2026","datePublished":"2026-04-22","dateModified":"2026-05-10","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Marco Vela"},"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1486325212027-8081e485255e?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1800&q=80"},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Core Web Vitals: Why UK B2B Sites Score Worse Than US Equivalents","description":"British marketing sites consistently fail Core Web Vitals at higher rates than US peers. We dug into 200 .co.uk sites and identified the five recurring causes — and how to fix them.","url":"https://sterlingember.com/blog/core-web-vitals-uk-b2b-sites","datePublished":"2026-03-30","dateModified":"2026-05-04","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Theo Ember"},"image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551434678-e076c223a692?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1800&q=80"},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"UK GDPR & The ICO's New Cookie Guidance: What Your Marketing Site Must Do","description":"The ICO updated its cookie guidance in January 2026. Most UK marketing sites are now technically non-compliant. Here's the practical checklist that keeps you legal and your analytics working.","url":"https://sterlingember.com/blog/uk-gdpr-cookie-guidance-2026","datePublished":"2026-02-18","dateModified":"2026-04-12","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Avery Sterling"},"image":